<HEADLINE>
<P>
EARTH'S RESOURCES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Thank you for running the piece headlined "Plunder of Earth Began With Man" on 
June 10. 
</P>
<P>
 It seems to me that the net lesson for us is that our generation and that of 
our children have a great opportunity and bear a correspondingly heavy 
burden.While our science has put into our hands more efficient means for 
plundering the Earth than ever before, and our worldwide economic system 
increases the short-term profit to be gained by doing so, our science at the 
same time gives us better tools than ever before to understand the consequences 
of what we do and to devise better alternatives, and our democratic political 
system (despite its flaws) gives us as citizens more power than ever before to 
influence, or even control, what is done. 
</P>
<P>
 If we use those scientific tools and that political power, we can avoid the 
mistakes of past cultures and preserve our planet. 
</P>
<P>
 ROBERT A. FLETCHER 
</P>
<P>
 Rancho Palos Verdes 
</P>
</TEXT>
