<TEXT>
<P>
 Venezuela's Planning Minister Quits: The official in charge of long-term 
economic planning quit because of disputes with the government on how to rally 
Venezuela's foundering economy. Planning Minister Luis Carlos Palacios said he 
disagreed with government plans announced last week to impose price and 
exchange controls. He also said the government had ignored a broad economic 
plan put forward by his ministry that included increasing the prices for fuel, 
modifications to the social security system and intensified talks with the 
International Monetary Fund. 
</P>
