<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: COUNTYWIDE; FREE SCREENINGS FOR BREAST CANCER OFFERED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JON NALICK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Free screenings for breast cancer will be offered Friday through July 13 to 
women in Fullerton, Santa Ana and San Juan Capistrano. 
</P>
<P>
 The screenings, by the San Clemente-based Susan G. Komen Breast Cancer 
Foundation, will be offered to women over 40 and women of any age whose mothers 
or sisters had cancer before age 50. 
</P>
<P>
 Eligibility also is based on financial need and appointments are required, 
spokeswoman Sally Coombe said. 
</P>
<P>
 The first screening will be Friday at the Fullerton Senior Center, 340 W. 
Commonwealth Ave. Other screenings include those at: 
</P>
<P>
 * Spurgeon United Methodist Church, 1025 W. Memory Lane, Santa Ana, on Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 * South County Community Clinic, 33081 Calle Perfecto, Suite A, San Juan 
Capistrano, on July 13. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information and appointments, call (714) 496-5624. JON NALICK 
</P>
