<P>
WORLD CUP USA '94: ROUND OF 16; SPOTLIGHT; OR THEME FROM 'DALLAS' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By HELENE ELLIOTT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 There was no scoreboard to prompt them, as there is at most arenas and 
stadiums, but fans in the Florida Citrus Bowl had no problems amusing 
themselves Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 A band, in colors of the Netherlands, kept the crowd singing with a varied 
repertoire, including, "Battle Hymn of the Republic," "Auld Lang Syne," "Those 
Were the Days," "They Call the Wind Mariah" and "California, Here We Come." 
</P>
<P>
 The Dutch team's next game is in Texas, so maybe they should have added, "The 
Eyes of Texas." HELENE ELLIOTT 
</P>
