129 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD CUP USA '94: ROUND OF 16; SPOTLIGHT; WARMING UP IN ITALY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRIS DUFRESNE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Americans are traditionalists when it comes to pregame hosts. We have Bob 
Costas and Greg Gumbel. 
</P>
<P>
 In Italy, however, pregame World Cup coverage on RAI, the state broadcasting 
company, begins with an hourlong burlesque show, hosted by Valeria Marini and 
Alba Parietti. 
</P>
<P>
 "Palpitating Valeria and pounding Alba are the first soubrettes to have been 
given the job of hosting a soccer program," London's Sunday Telegraph reports. 
</P>
<P>
 An estimated 7 million Italians reportedly tune in. 
</P>
<P>
 The women admittedly don't know much about soccer X's and O's, so they spend 
most of the hour on the stage in various stages of undress. 
</P>
<P>
 "Being vapid is my job," Valeria is quoted as saying. "You need a bit of 
silliness to help distract people from everyday problems." CHRIS DUFRESNE 
</P>
</TEXT>
