REGIONAL ROUNDUP: APPAREL MAKER RECEIVES PROPOSALS FROM 2 INVESTORS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Cherokee Inc., the debt-heavy Sunland apparel maker, announced it has received 
proposals from two investors that could lead to infusions of cash equity. 
</P>
<P>
 Both proposals require concessions from holders of Cherokee's 11% senior 
subordinated notes due in 1999, but neither would affect trade creditors, the 
company said. 
</P>
