REGIONAL ROUNDUP: ORDERS INCREASE FOR MAKER OF CAST ALUMINUM WHEELS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Superior Industries International Inc., a Van Nuys maker of cast aluminum 
wheels, said General Motors Corp. has increased orders of its aluminum wheels 
for pickups by about 20% due to climbing sales of GM's light trucks. 
</P>
<P>
 Superior projected that the additional orders will boost its revenues by about 
$10 million per year. 
</P>
<P>
 The company said it will begin making the additional wheels in August and 
continue supplying them for the life of the product. Superior reported revenue 
of $393 million for the year ending Dec. 31. 
