<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY REVIEW: TELEDYNE RECEIVES ORDER FOR FRIEND-OR-FOE SYSTEM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Jack Searles 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Teledyne Electronics in Newbury Park has received a $63.8-million order from 
the Air Force for devices that help aircraft pilots identify targets as friend 
or foe. 
</P>
<P>
 The contract calls for the Ventura County unit of Los Angeles-based Teledyne 
Inc. to deliver 200 of the systems by June, 1998. The systems will be installed 
in F-16 jet fighters that will be delivered to the air forces of South Korea 
and Turkey. 
</P>
<P>
 A Teledyne spokesman said the order is the first production go-ahead for the 
AN / APX-109 Advanced Identification Friend or Foe system. He said the order 
should stabilize the payroll at Teledyne Electronics, but that he didn't know 
whether new hirings would result. 
</P>
</TEXT>
