<HEADLINE>
<P>
CYCLING WITHOUT HELMET IS BAD NEWS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 I was quite dismayed to see your front-page story in today's Orange County 
edition. Your photography accompanying the article "Wheels of Fortune" (June 
24) describing the new "lowrider" bicycle showed five children and teen-agers 
riding without bicycle helmets. I am sure it is very "cool" to have one of 
these decked-out cycles, and, indeed, they may even help keep some kid out of a 
gang and trouble, but any one of those kids could end up with a severe 
traumatic head injury because he or she was not wearing a helmet. 
</P>
<P>
 JOANNE LEVY 
</P>
<P>
 Rossmoor 
</P>
