ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: BREA; RETIRED POLICE OFFICER PLANS COUNCIL BID 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALAN EYERLY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Citing concerns about the city's financial management, Marty Simonoff has 
announced his intention to run for City Council in the November election. 
</P>
<P>
 Simonoff, 43, is a retired captain with the Huntington Park Police 
Department.The 13-year Brea resident now works with his family-owned recycling 
and trash hauling business. 
</P>
<P>
 "I am very concerned that the city will not be able to maintain essential 
public services with a budget deficit estimated in excess of $2 million," 
Simonoff said. 
</P>
<P>
 "For the city to operate in a more efficient and effective manner than in the 
past, a realignment, consolidation, partnership or restructuring of city 
operations is needed. Additionally, the city must also re-evaluate the impact 
of redevelopment on the revenue sources available." 
</P>
<P>
 Simonoff, who is making his first bid for public office, said he is also 
concerned about increasing the number of activities and facilities for youth. 
</P>
<P>
 His wife, Sonie, is a teacher's aide at Brea Olinda High School. Their 
daughter is a junior at the high school, and their son is a seventh-grader at 
Brea Junior High School.ALAN EYERLY 
</P>
