ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: COUNTYWIDE; LOCAL PAGEANTS TO BE SHOWN ON CABLE TV 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BERT ELJERA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The selection and crowning of this year's Miss Orange County U.S.A. and Miss 
Orange County Teen U.S.A. will be broadcast on local cable television in north 
Orange County today. 
</P>
<P>
 The two-hour program can be seen on Comcast Cablevision Channel 55 in Buena 
Park and on Channel 65 in Fullerton and Placentia. 
</P>
<P>
 The telecast begins at 7 p.m. The program will be replayed July 6 and July 12, 
also at 7 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Bob Keller, executive producer of the show, said it will be the first telecast 
of the pageant, which was held in May in Brea and in which 23 contestants 
participated. 
</P>
<P>
 Cari DeBoard of Tustin was voted Miss Orange County U.S.A., and Valerie Masse 
of Buena Park won the Miss Orange County Teen U.S.A. title. 
</P>
<P>
 They will represent the county in the Miss California U.S.A. contest on Labor 
Day at Cal State Long Beach. 
</P>
<P>
 Winners of the state contest will move on to the Miss U.S.A. and Miss Teen 
U.S.A. pageants later this year. 
</P>
<P>
 The teen candidates range in age from 14 to 17, and Miss U.S.A. contestants 
are 18 to 26 years old. BERT ELJERA 
</P>
