<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: IRVINE; EX-SOUTH VIETNAM LEADER TO GIVE TALK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The former commander-in-chief of the South Vietnamese Army and former 
president of the Republic of Vietnam, Gen. Nguyen Khanh, is scheduled to 
address the Orange County Forum, a public affairs organization. 
</P>
<P>
 His talk, titled "The Economic War for Vietnam," is expected to focus on the 
possibility of Vietnam becoming a colony of China if the United States does not 
immediately invest in its economy. 
</P>
<P>
 Khanh was born in South Vietnam in 1927. He graduated from a French military 
academy in 1947 and pursued a military career. He became South Vietnam's chief 
of state in 1964 but was overthrown in a coup d'etat in 1965 and left Saigon 
for Europe. 
</P>
<P>
 In 1977 he immigrated to the United States and now lives in the San Francisco 
area with his wife, Nguyen Le Tran, and four of their six children. 
</P>
<P>
 Khanh will speak at an Orange County Forum luncheon meeting, scheduled for 
11:30 a.m. Thursday at the Hyatt Regency Irvine, 17900 Jamboree Road. Admission 
is $25 for forum members and $35 for non-members. For reservations, call (714) 
588-9884. 
</P>
</TEXT>
