<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: 1 KILLED, 2 INJURED IN OXNARD COLLISION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PEGGY Y. LEE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 75-year-old Lancaster man was killed Monday in the first fatal traffic 
accident in Ventura County over the Fourth of July weekend, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The man, whose identity was not released pending notification of next of kin, 
made an illegal left turn in front of an oncoming car at Victoria Avenue and 
Channel Islands Boulevard, Oxnard Police Officer John Ahearn said. 
</P>
<P>
 About 12:20 p.m., the victim was driving east on Channel Islands Boulevard, 
then made a left turn onto Victoria Avenue against the traffic light, Ahearn 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 He slammed into a car traveling west on Channel Islands Boulevard driven by 
Nerces Eykjian, 18, of Oxnard. Eykjian and his passenger, Robyn Hamilton, were 
listed in fair condition Monday night at St. John's Regional Medical Center in 
Oxnard. 
</P>
<P>
 In addition to investigating the fatal crash, authorities on Monday reported 
fewer drunk-driving arrests in Ventura County over the holiday weekend this 
year. 
</P>
<P>
 As of Monday afternoon, the California Highway Patrol had arrested 26 
motorists on suspicion of drunk driving since the start of the Fourth of July 
weekend, compared to 33 during the same period last year. PEGGY Y. LEE 
</P>
</TEXT>
