WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: VENTURA; POLICE SET UP 2ND STOREFRONT STATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRISTINA LIMA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In an effort to reduce crime and improve community relations, the Ventura 
Police Department will open a second storefront station Thursday, this time 
behind the Vons shopping center at Main Street and Ventura Avenue. 
</P>
<P>
 An opening ceremony will begin at 10 a.m. at the new storefront, located at 
110 N. Olive Ave.Students from Sheridan Way School, Westpark Kids recreational 
group, and the Boys and Girls Club will entertain visitors with music and other 
activities. 
</P>
<P>
 The storefront's opening comes about two months after hundreds of Ventura 
Avenue-area residents complained to City Council members about crime and gangs. 
Some residents told the council that gang members had thrown stones at their 
windows and threatened them. 
</P>
<P>
 Similar to a storefront on Bristol Road, space for the new mini-station was 
donated by a local business. The office will be staffed with two Police 
Department employees and volunteers. CHRISTINA LIMA 
