<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: SIMI VALLEY; DUMP SITE REOPENS FOR QUAKE DEBRIS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SARA CATANIA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Simi Valley free dumping site for earthquake debris is reopening today. 
</P>
<P>
 The city decided to reopen the site, which has been closed since February, to 
assist residents who are repairing damage caused by the Jan. 17 earthquake. 
</P>
<P>
 The site, located on Alamo Street near Tapo Canyon Road, will be open Mondays 
through Saturdays from 9 a.m. to 2 p.m. through Nov. 5. 
</P>
<P>
 Residents must unload their own vehicles and present a driver's license with a 
local address or other proof of residency. 
</P>
<P>
 Materials that will be accepted include block walls, concrete, asphalt, brick, 
stucco, Sheetrock and plaster. 
</P>
<P>
 Dumping of appliances, yard waste, tires, hazardous waste and household trash 
will not be allowed. For more information, call 583-6753. SARA CATANIA 
</P>
</TEXT>
