<HEADLINE>
<P>
SANTA CLARITA / ANTELOPE VALLEY; APARTMENT GUARD IS SHOT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARK SABBATINI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An armed security guard was shot in the shoulder at an apartment complex in 
east Newhall by a man wielding a handgun who demanded the guard leave or be 
gunned down, a sheriff's official said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 The shooting occurred about 11:40 p.m. Sunday in the 24000 block of Pine 
Street, said Lt. Art Valenzuela of the Santa Clarita Valley Sheriff's 
Station.The gunman, described as a male Hispanic about 18 to 22 years old, 
remains at large. 
</P>
<P>
 Dago Natareno, 38, was listed in stable condition Monday evening at Henry Mayo 
Newhall Memorial Hospital in Valencia, Valenzuela said. Officials said they do 
not know what city Natareno lives in. 
</P>
<P>
 "He told us (that) prior to the shooting the occupants of a maroon Chevrolet 
Monte Carlo had driven by and said if he did not leave the area he would be 
shot," Valenzuela said. 
</P>
<P>
 Shortly afterward, the gunman stepped between two apartment buildings Natareno 
was guarding and fired four shots from a small caliber handgun, Valenzuela 
said. Natareno did not return fire. MARK SABBATINI 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA070594-0186 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 057811 </DOCID>
