</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOYS AND THEIR TOYS; GI JOE TRIVIA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAVID WHARTON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * Names originally considered for GI Joe: Salty the Sailor, Ace the Pilot, 
Rocky the Marine. 
</P>
<P>
 * The scar on Joe's cheek represents more than machismo.It was the only way 
Hasbro could trademark his face. Similarly, early prototypes featured a 
misplaced thumbnail that was incorporated into the design as another protection 
against copyright infringement. 
</P>
<P>
 * If Joe were built to human scale, he would stand 5 feet, 9 inches tall. 
</P>
<P>
 * Perhaps the most collectable GI Joe is the female version, which was 
discontinued afer one year. A mint-condition GI Nurse Action Girl sold for 
almost $5,000 at a toy show last year. 
</P>
<P>
 * Last fall, a group of performance artists in the East Village of Manhattan 
purchased as many as 300 "Talking Duke" GI Joes and "Teen Talk" Barbies and 
switched their voice mechanisms. They were able to sneak the toys back onto 
store shelves in at least two states. A number of boys who bought the miniature 
fighting man home were startled to hear him utter, in a high-pitched 
voice,"Let's plan our dream wedding!" 
</P>
<P>
 Sources: Hasbro, Inc. and "The Complete Encyclopedia to GI Joe." DAVID WHARTON 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
