Center in Golden, Colo., estimated the magnitude of the quake at 6.0. The quake 
was centered about 325 miles southeast of Mexico City, off the Pacific coast of 
Oaxaca state, the center said. It was felt strongly in the state capital of 
Oaxaca, a colonial town popular with tourists. Two masons were killed when the 
quake brought down a wall they were working on in the city center. 
