</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
BABY KILLED, 6 HURT IN DOWNTOWN L.A. CRASH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 6-month-old boy was killed and six other people were injured in the 
collision of a pickup truck and another vehicle Monday night in Downtown Los 
Angeles. The unidentified child died of cardiac arrest shortly after being 
taken to California Hospital Medical Center, a hospital spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
 Two children were flown from the scene at Olympic Boulevard and Hill Street to 
Childrens Hospital in a Los Angeles Fire Department air ambulance, spokesman 
Brian Humphrey said. The cause of the accident was under investigation, police 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 A total of four children and three adults were hurt in the crash. Most of the 
injuries occurred when the pickup rolled over several times and its occupants, 
riding inside a camper shell, were ejected, Humphrey said. 
</P>
