<HEADLINE>
<P>
WHERE ARE THEY NOW?; TIM FOLI 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Times staff writer David W. Myers catches up with former Dodgers and Angels. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Foli, a three-sport standout at Notre Dame High in Sherman Oaks, came to the 
Angels in 1982 in a deal that sent Brian Harper to Milwaukee.The fiery 
shortstop led the league in fielding that year and helped the club to its 
second divisional title. He was traded to the Yankees after the 1983 season and 
retired in '85 with a lifetime .251 average. 
</P>
<P>
 Foli, who turned down a football scholarship at USC to pursue his baseball 
career, is in his third year as the infield and first-base coach for the 
Brewers. Now 43, he spends the off-season hunting, fishing and playing golf 
near his Florida home. 
